# Skill Trigger Mandatory Policy

- Skills are required process tools, not optional helpers.
- If a task matches a trigger, run the matching skill before implementation.

## Trigger Matrix

- Rule/governance updates -> run create-rule skill first.
- Figma/UI alignment tasks -> run UI/design workflow and verify token/state coverage.
- Editor/runtime config tasks -> run update settings workflow before edits.
- New reusable AI workflow -> run create-skill workflow.

## Gate Checks

- No "done" if required skill was skipped.
- If skill guidance conflicts with project rules, follow project rules and document deviation.
- Always include a short "skill used" note in delivery summary:
  - skill name
  - why triggered
  - what decisions it enforced
